Ascent
/* * Question Bank */
// Morning Anchors and Rotations Who am I choosing to be today? Name it clearly — your brain acts on the identity it rehearses What will I not tolerate from myself today? Proactive inhibition — name the behavior before it shows up. What is my single non-negotiable today? One thing. If everything else burns, this gets done. Which of your roles needs the most attention today — and what does that look like? What fear or resistance might show up today, and how will the person you\'re becoming respond to it? What would the person you\'re trying to be do in the first hour of today? What story about yourself are you ready to stop confirming today? If your future self could see today, what would they be proud of? What standard do you tend to lower when no one is watching? Will you hold it today? What does your body need from you today to perform as you expect? What is the gap between who you say you are and how you behaved yesterday — and how do you close it today? Which role in your identity has been getting the least from you lately? What decision today, if made with full integrity, would change the trajectory of your week? What limiting belief is trying to run the show today — and what is the truth that replaces it? How will you show up for the people in your life today in a way consistent with who you\'re becoming? What are you tolerating that someone with your identity would not? What does discipline look like for you today — specifically, not generally? What would you have to believe about yourself to make today excellent?
// Evening Anchors and Rotations Did I act like the person I said I would be? Direct identity audit — be honest, not harsh Where did I fall short — and what was the real reason? Reframe failure as data. The real reason is rarely what it seems. What is the one correction I carry into tomorrow? Implementation intention — specific beats vague every time Which of your roles did you fully show up for today — and which one got a lesser version of you? What thought pattern ran on repeat today? Is it the pattern of the person you\'re becoming? Where did you make a decision based on who you used to be instead of who you\'re choosing to be? What did you say yes to today that someone with your identity would have said no to? What uncomfortable thing did you avoid today, and what does that avoidance cost you? Where did you operate from fear rather than from your declared identity? What did your body tell you today that your ego ignored? If you replayed today as an outside observer, what would you tell yourself to do differently? What habit either confirmed or undermined your identity today? Who did you influence today — and was that influence consistent with who you say you are? What were you pretending not to know about yourself today? What standard did you hold even when it was hard? What does that tell you about yourself? Where did you shrink when you could have stepped fully into your identity? What did you learn about yourself today that you want to remember in a year? What unfinished emotional or mental business is following you into tomorrow? How did your energy levels affect your ability to live your identity today? What conversation did you have — or avoid — that your identity required? What pattern are you finally ready to interrupt — and what replaces it? Where in your day did you feel most like the person you\'re trying to become? If today were a chapter in the story of who you became, what would its title be? // Weekly Looking at your wins, how did you prove your new identity this week? What neural pathway (old habit) tried to pull you back, and how will you interrupt it next week? If you were already the 100% version of your [Role], what would they do differently next week?
What is one area where you were "playing small" this week, and how will you expand next week? Which of your values did you embody most consistently this week? What was the most important lesson you learned about yourself during a moment of failure this week? If you could change one decision you made this week, what would it be and why? How has your identity evolved over the last seven days?
Your Identity Define who you are, not what you do. I am " a disciplined athlete" This person, every day: MY DAILY STANDARDS Train Auto-validated with your sessions Add standard 💡 Training standards are auto-validated when you complete a session. The rest you mark yourself. +%d XP/day
MY ROLES Add role New Role Role name Athlete, Trader, Reader… Add roles to organize your standards
New Standard What does this person do every day? Type Role +%d XP per day when fulfilled Add Standard Select a role
Back Skip Next Mirror Mode: If the person you want to become could see today\\\'s version of you — what would they say? No progress today Almost perfect Partially aligned Below your standards No progress today Identity accomplished
